d","1580–Male":"1580–Afdød","1515–1569":"1515–1569","1522–1614":"1522–1614","about 1580":"omkring 1580","23 October 1600":"23. oktober 1600","1580":"1580","1547":"1547","1569":"1569","1567":"1567","1600":"1600","1522":"1522","20 Jul 1577":"20. juli 1577","1615":"1615","1614":"1614","1515":"1515","1603":"1603","1548":"1548","Bolton, Lancashire, England":"Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","St Peter Churchyard, Bolton, Metropolitan Borough of Bolton, Greater Manchester, England":"Saint Peter Churchyard, Bolton, Greater Manchester, England, United Kingdom","St Bartholomew, Great Harwood, Lancashire, England":"Harwood, Lancashire, England"},"nl":{"1547–23 October 1600":"1547–23 oktober 1600","1547–1600":"1547–1600","1548–1603":"1548–1603","1567–1615":"1567–1615","1567–Male":"1567–Overleden","1580–Male":"1580–Overleden","1515–1569":"1515–1569","1522–1614":"1522–1614","about 1580":"circa 1580","23 October 1600":"23 oktober 1600","1580":"1580","1547":"1547","1569":"1569","1567":"1567","1600":"1600","1522":"1522","20 Jul 1577":"20 juli 1577","1615":"1615","1614":"1614","1515":"1515","1603":"1603","1548":"1548","Bolton, Lancashire, England":"Bolton, Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Bolton, Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","St Peter Churchyard, Bolton, Metropolitan Borough of Bolton, Greater Manchester, England":"Saint Peter Churchyard, Bolton, Greater Manchester, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","St Bartholomew, Great Harwood, Lancashire, England":"Harwood, Lancashire, England"},"en":{"1547–23 October 1600":"1547–23 October 1600","1547–1600":"1547–1600","1548–1603":"1548–1603","1567–1615":"1567–1615","1567–Male":"1567–Deceased","1580–Male":"1580–Deceased","1515–1569":"1515–1569","1522–1614":"1522–1614","about 1580":"about 1580","23 October 1600":"23 October 1600","1580":"1580","1547":"1547","1569":"1569","1567":"1567","1600":"1600","1522":"1522","20 Jul 1577":"20 July 1577","1615":"1615","1614":"1614","1515":"1515","1603":"1603","1548":"1548","Bolton, Lancashire, England":"Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","St Peter Churchyard, Bolton, Metropolitan Borough of Bolton, Greater Manchester, England":"Saint Peter Churchyard, Bolton, Greater Manchester, England, United Kingdom","St Bartholomew, Great Harwood, Lancashire, England":"Harwood, Lancashire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Aimsworth","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from a place near Manchester named Ainsworth, from the Old English personal name <i>Ægen</i> + Old English <i>worth</i> ‘enclosure’.","English (Yorkshire): in Yorkshire the name was a variant of, or confused with   Hainsworth  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hainsworth","meanings":["English:","(Yorkshire): habitational name from Hainworth in Keighley, Yorkshire, named from the Old English personal name <i>Hagena</i> + Old English <i>worth</i> ‘enclosure’. The intrusive <i>-s-</i> was acquired by the late 15th century, probably through false association with the Lancashire surname <i>Ainsworth</i> in 2 below.","variant of   Ainsworth   in Lancashire. Names such as <i>de Haynesworth</i> and <i>de Heynesworth</i> occur in the surrounding area in the 14th century."]}]},{"name":"Gyles","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Giles ."],"variants":[{"name":"Giles","meanings":["Much altered English vernacular form of the Late Latin name <i>Aegidius</i>, from Greek <i>Aigidios</i> (a derivative of <i>aigidion</i> ‘kid, young goat’), via Old French <i>Gide</i>. It was the name of an 8th‐century saint who, according to tradition, was an Athenian citizen who fled to Provence because he could not cope with the fame and adulation caused by his power to work miracles, in particular by healing the lame and crippled. This was not a particularly common name in the Middle Ages and its use seems to have been confined to certain families and localities."]}]},{"name":"Henrie","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Henry</b> (  and <b>Heinrich</b> ), especially common in Denmark."],"variants":[{"name":"Henry","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gyles Henrie Aimsworth was born in 1547, in Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Aimsworth/Aynesworth, was 32 and his mother, Catherine Marsh, was 25. He married Lady Eline Dean on 20 July 1577, in Harwood, Lancashire, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died on 23 October 1600, in his hometown, at the age of 53, and was buried in Saint Peter Churchyard, Bolton, Greater Manchester, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1547–23 October 1600":"1547–23. oktoober 1600","1547–1600":"1547–1600","1548–1603":"1548–1603","1567–1615":"1567–1615","1567–Male":"1567–Surnud","1580–Male":"1580–Surnud","1515–1569":"1515–1569","1522–1614":"1522–1614","about 1580":"umbes 1580","23 October 1600":"23. oktoober 1600","1580":"1580","1547":"1547","1569":"1569","1567":"1567","1600":"1600","1522":"1522","20 Jul 1577":"20. juuli 1577","1615":"1615","1614":"1614","1515":"1515","1603":"1603","1548":"1548","Bolton, Lancashire, England